5D%20himself%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20historied%20and%20famous%20puzzle%20makers%20and%20has%20published%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20puzzles.%20This%20one%2C%20the%20Disappearing%20Bicyclist%20is%20one%20of%20my%20favorites%2C%20using%20a%20simple%20rotation%20to%20hide%20the%20secrets%20of%20the%20puzzle%2C%20yet%20show%20you%20in%20full%20plain%20sight%20how%20it%20is%20operating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22desktop-ad%22%3E%3Cdiv%20data-pw-desk%3D%22leaderboard_btf%22%20id%3D%22pwDeskLbBtf1%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20To%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20one%20is%20relatively%20simple%20to%20operate%2C%20count%20the%20bicyclists%20on%20the%20screen%2C%20and%20then%20click%20anywhere%20and%20count%20again%2C%20you%E2%80%99ll%20see%20that%20they%20go%20from%2013%20to%2012%2C%20and%20hence%20the%20conundrum%20will%20arrive%E2%80%A6%20where%20did%20the%20extra%20come%20from%20(or%20go!%3F)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExplain%20it%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20this%20case%2C%20while%20it%E2%80%99s%20tricky%20to%20see%20(especially%20in%20the%20analog%20format)%2C%20the%20boys%20are%20slithered%20away%20each%20by%20a%20little%20piece%2C%20they%20all%20will%20seem%20a%20little%20smaller%2C%20and%20when%20you%20do%20the%20full%20count%2C%20they%E2%80%99ll%20be%20no%20more.%20A%20nice%20way%20to%20approach%20it%20is%20by%20looking%20at%20and%20counting%20the%20flags%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20id%3D%22cites-and-extras%22%3ECites%20and%20Extras%3A%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%5B1%5D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FSam_Loyd%22%3ESam%20Loyd%20Wikipedia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20truly%20an%20interesting%20guy!%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mathpuzzle.com%2Floyd%2F%22%3ESam%20Loyds%20Cyclopedia%20of%205000%20puzzles%3C%2Fa%3E%20Sam%20Loyds%20Magnum%20Opus%2C%20a%20collection%20of%205000%20puzzles%2C%20published%20in%201914%20(Now%20in%20public%20domain!)%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22disclaimer%22%3EI'